{"word":"G3709 - ὀργή - orgḗ - or-gay' - Anger","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ὀργή</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>orgḗ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>or-gay'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Anger"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"கோபம், கோபாக்கினை - பெண்பால் பெயர்ச்சொல்"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"the natural disposition, temper, character; movement or agitation of soul, impulse, desire, any violent emotion."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Noun Feminine / பெயர்ச்சொல் (பெண்பால்)</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> From <a href=\"#/G3713 - ὀρέγομαι - orégomai - or-eg'-om-ahee/3713\">G3713</a>; properly <i>desire</i> (as a <i>reaching</i> forth or <i>excitement</i> of the mind), that is, (by analogy) violent <i>passion</i> (<i>ire</i>, or [justifiable] <i>abhorrence</i>); by implication <i>punishment:</i> - anger, indignation, vengeance, wrath."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3709 - ὀργή - orgḗ - or-gay'/3709\">G3709</a>, <a href=\"#/G3710 - ὀργίζω - orgízō - or-gid'-zo/3710\">G3710</a>, <a href=\"#/G3711 - ὀργίλος - orgílos - org-ee'-los/3711\">G3711</a>, <a href=\"#/G3949 - παροργίζω - parorgízō - par-org-id'-zo/3949\">G3949</a>, <a href=\"#/G3950 - παροργισμός - parorgismós - par-org-is-mos'/3950\">G3950</a>"}]}